Dear Investors,

We are writing to inform you of a recent attempted fraud incident involving=
 one of our investors. In this case, a third party gained unauthorized acce=
ss to the investor=92s email account and sent a falsified version of our ca=
pital call notice. The fraudulent notice included altered bank account deta=
ils, directing funds to an illegitimate account.

PLEASE NOTE THAT THE FUND HAS NOT CHANGED ITS BANK ACCOUNT DETAILS. All leg=
itimate capital call notices from us will reference the same account inform=
ation you have previously used.

To protect yourself and your organization against similar threats, we ask t=
hat you please follow these precautions:

  1.  Always verify any changes in bank account details verbally with us, u=
sing contact information you already have on file =96 do not rely on contac=
t details provided in any email or document, as these may also be fraudulen=
t.
  2.  Be alert to any unexpected or unusual emails requesting fund transfer=
s or account changes, especially those marked as urgent.
  3.  If in doubt, pause and call us directly to confirm the authenticity o=
f the request.

We take security and investor communication seriously and are implementing =
additional internal measures to protect against these types of threats. If =
you have any questions or concerns, please don=92t hesitate to contact us d=
irectly.

Thank you
Eran Raz

